## 2. Configuration de l'application

### Structure de configuration

L'application démarre vierge. Vous devez charger une configuration d'usine via un fichier JSON.

#### Exemple de fichier de configuration française (`config_fr.json`)

```json
{
  "version": "1.0",
  "language": "fr",
  "company": "Mon Entreprise",
  "sites": [
    {
      "name": "Usine Lyon",
      "location": "Confluence",
      "buildings": [
        {
          "name": "Atelier Production",
          "workshops": [
            {
              "name": "Ligne CNC",
              "machines": [
                {
                  "name": "CNC Fanuc 300i",
                  "type": "CNC Lathe",
                  "status": "running",
                  "description": "Tour CNC haute précision"
                },
                {
                  "name": "5-Axis DMG UGV",
                  "type": "Machining Center",
                  "status": "idle",
                  "description": "Centre d'usinage 5 axes"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Exemple de fichier de configuration anglaise (`config_en.json`)

```json
{
  "version": "1.0",
  "language": "en",
  "company": "My Company",
  "sites": [
    {
      "name": "Lyon Plant",
      "location": "Confluence",
      "buildings": [
        {
          "name": "Production Workshop",
          "workshops": [
            {
              "name": "CNC Line",
              "machines": [
                {
                  "name": "Fanuc 300i CNC Lathe",
                  "type": "CNC Lathe",
                  "status": "running",
                  "description": "High precision CNC lathe"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Chargement de la configuration

1. **Via l'interface web** :
   - Aller sur http://localhost:5173
   - Se connecter avec un compte admin (admin@oee.local / Admin1234!)
   - Aller dans "Configuration" → "Importer configuration"
   - Sélectionner votre fichier `config_fr.json` ou `config_en.json`
   - Cliquer sur "Importer"

2. **Via l'API** :
```bash
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/config/import" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  -F "file=@config_fr.json"
```

